    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh, Bartholomäus Haller von Hallerstain and János
                    Dubraviczky to Banská Bystrica Town Council (Kremnica, 17 February 1541)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>They say at Queen Mary’s order that they should make sure the inheritance
                            of her cook, Georg Rockelfinger, should be paid out on both his mother’s
                            and his father’s side, which is with them, in Banská Bystrica.
                            Rockelfinger’s inheritance should be handed over to Oláh without delay,
                            so that the plaintiff can receive it, as is fair.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Namhafft, ersam unnd weiß lieb hern unnd freundt, unnser freundlich
                    diennst sein euch zuvor! </p>
                <p>Unns hat unnser <persName>genedigiste fraw</persName><note
                        type="critic">Queen Mary.</note> bevolhen, euch zu sagen, das ir
                        <persName>Jeorg Rockelfinger</persName>,<note type="critic">Georg
                        Rockelfinger. We only know one document on him, his father’s last will from
                        1536, see <hi rend="smallcap">Meier–Piirainen–Wegera</hi> 2009, 256.</note>
                    ir mt.<note type="critic">I.e. ihrer Majestät.</note> kuchenmaister, umb sein
                    angepurrender tail seines erlebten vetterlichen unnd mutterlichen erbs bey euch,
                    in dem <placeName>Neuensol</placeName>, unverzogenliche bezalung verschaffenn
                    solt. Derhalben von wegen höchtsgenanter unnser <persName>genedigisten
                        frawen</persName> unnser bevellich fur unns selbst freundtlich pittendt, ir
                    wellt ime <persName>Rockelfynger</persName> sollchen seinen gepurrendenn tail
                    one verner verzug zu hern <persName>Nicolaus Olaus</persName> hannden
                    verschaffen unnd ime unclaghafft machen, wie dan an im selbst recht unnd pillich
                    ist. Das wel wir unns anstat unnser gennedigsten frawen zu beschehen verlassen
                    und thun, was euch lieb ist. </p>
                <p>Datum <placeName>Cremnitz</placeName> den XVII. tag Februarii anno
                    Domini XXXXI<hi rend="super">o</hi>.</p>
                <p><seg type="signature"><add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">Nicolaus
                            Olahus custos Albensis etc.</add></seg></p>
                <p><seg type="signature"><add corresp="author" type="insert">Bartholmes
                            Haller vom Hallerstain<note type="critic">Bartholomäus Haller von
                                Hallerstein (1486–1551) was Secretary to Mary of Hungary.</note>
                            etc.</add></seg></p>
                <p><seg type="signature"><add corresp="author" type="insert">Jonnes
                            Dubrawiczki</add></seg><note type="critic">János Dubraviczky.</note></p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso">
                <head>On the outer side:</head>
                <p>Den namhafften, ersamen unnd weisen hern, richtern, rat unnd gemain
                    der stat Neuensol, unnsern hern unnd freundenn.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
